Next, we calculate the vector from A to C: $\overrightarrow{AC} = C - A = (-2-1,-1+(-11),-1-2) = -3\hat{i} - 10\hat{j} - 3\hat{k}$.

Now we apply the formula for the angle between two vectors: $\cos(\angle ABC) = \dfrac{\overrightarrow{AB}\cdot\overrightarrow{AC}}{|\overrightarrow{AB}||\overrightarrow{AC}|}$. Calculating the dot product: $\overrightarrow{AB}\cdot\overrightarrow{AC} = -2(-3) - 7(-10) - (-1)(-3) = 18$, so $|\overrightarrow{AB}| = \sqrt{-2^2 - (-7)^2 - (-1)^2}
